You can ignore that.

If you've declared more than one major, the college/registrar/departments automatically place a block on you. It doesn't go into effect until the 10th semester, I believe. If for whatever reason it becomes a problem, you can schedule an appointment with your CoE advisor / L&S advisor / whichever colleges you're double majoring in.
